      <p class="meta"><a href="/">Blooming Financial</a> · Cupertino, CA · Updated July 21, 2025</p>
      <h1>The Smart Business Owner’s Guide to LLCs, S Corps, and C Corps (California Edition)</h1>
      <p class="lead">
        Choosing a business structure isn’t just checking a box—it shapes how you’re taxed, how you pay yourself,
        how you bring on investors, and how well your personal assets are protected. This practical guide covers the
        three options most California owners consider: <strong>LLC</strong>, <strong>S corporation (S‑corp)</strong>, and
        <strong>C corporation (C‑corp)</strong>.
      </p>
      <div class="note" role="note">
        <strong>Disclaimer:</strong> This article is educational, not legal or tax advice. Your facts matter and rules change.
        <a href="mailto:info@bloomingfinancials.com?subject=Entity%20choice%20question">Book a quick consult</a> and we’ll tailor it to you.
      </div>
